#: includes/class-tih-settings.php:17
msgid "Configure cache lifetime, display theme, and learn how to use the TodayInHistory plugin. 
Data is fetched from the public \"On This Day\" API by byabbe.se (English only for event descriptions). 
Plugin interface and labels can be translated via standard WordPress language files (.po/.mo). 
Use the shortcode to display historical data on any page or post.
Examples:
[tih] — Displays today’s events (default).
[tih type="births" limit="5"] — Displays the 5 most recent notable births for today.
[tih type="deaths" month="8" day="14"] — Displays notable deaths for August 14, regardless of the year.
Available parameters:
type — "events" (default), "births", or "deaths".
limit — Maximum number of items to display (integer).
month — Month number (1–12) for a specific date.
day — Day of the month (1–31) for a specific date.
